The paper deals with network proximity computations, which are commonly used in data mining applications such as link prediction and collaborative filtering. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Databases (cs.DB), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The focus on efficient computation of Katz index and link prediction queries further supports these sub-categories.
